## Multi-Step Forms

Use multi-step forms when a single form has more than 6-8 fields or when the fields are logically grouped into distinct stages (e.g. an onboarding wizard).

### State Management for Steps

```tsx
"use client";

const STEPS = ["basics", "details", "review"] as const;
type Step = typeof STEPS[number];

export function MultiStepForm() {
  const [currentStep, setCurrentStep] = useState<Step>("basics");
  // Use react-hook-form with a combined schema or per-step schemas
  const form = useForm<WizardFormValues>({
    resolver: zodResolver(wizardSchema),
    mode: "onTouched",
  });

  const stepIndex = STEPS.indexOf(currentStep);

  const goNext = async () => {
    // Validate only the current step's fields before advancing
    const valid = await form.trigger(STEP_FIELDS[currentStep]);
    if (valid) setCurrentStep(STEPS[stepIndex + 1]);
  };

  const goPrev = () => setCurrentStep(STEPS[stepIndex - 1]);

  return (
    <>
      <StepIndicator steps={STEPS} currentStep={currentStep} />
      <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
        {currentStep === "basics" && <BasicsStep form={form} />}
        {currentStep === "details" && <DetailsStep form={form} />}
        {currentStep === "review" && <ReviewStep form={form} />}

        <FormNavigation
          isFirstStep={stepIndex === 0}
          isLastStep={stepIndex === STEPS.length - 1}
          onBack={goPrev}
          onNext={goNext}
          isSubmitting={form.formState.isSubmitting}
        />
      </form>
    </>
  );
}
```

### Step Indicator

```
[1: Basics] ---- [2: Details] ---- [3: Review]
  (complete)       (current)        (upcoming)
```

- Completed steps show a checkmark icon
- Current step shows a filled circle
- Upcoming steps show an outline circle
- Each step label is a button only when the step is already completed (allow going back, not skipping ahead)

